   2. EBS throughput Optimized HDD
   3. EBS General Purpose SSD
   4. EFS

6. A team is building an application that must persist and index JSON files in a highly-available data store. Latency of data access must remain consistent despite very high application traffic. Which service should the team choose?

7. The security policy of an organization requires an application to encrypt data before writing to the disk. Which solution should the organization use to meet this requirement?
   1. KMS API                       \(Correct\)
   2. AWS Certificate Manager        
   3. API Gateway with STS              \(Security Token Service，使你能请求临时credentials和IAM users\)
   4. IAM Access Key
8. A website runs on EC2 instances behind an ELB Application Load Balancer. The instances run in an Auto Scaling group across multiple Availability Zones. The instances deliver several large files \(images, PDFs, etc.\) that are stored on a shared Amazon EFS file system. The company needs to avoid serving the files from EC2 instances every time a user requests these digital assets.
   1. Move the digital assets to Amazon Glacier
   2. Cache static content using CloudFront               \(Correct. 因为要避免多次访问，必然需要增加缓存cache\)
   3. Resize the images so that they are smaller
   4. User reserved EC2 instances.
9. An application will read and write small objects to an S3 bucket. When the application is fully deployed, the read/write traffic will be very high. How should the architect maximize Amazon S3 performance?
   1. Prefix each object name with a random string.
   2. Use the STANDARD\_ID storage class
   3. Prefix each object name with the current date.       \(Correct\)
   4. Enable versioning on the S3 bucket.              \(Wrong selected.\)
10. 根据S3新的使用声明，S3请求速率性能的提高消除了任何先前的指南，即随机化对象前缀以实现更快的性能。
11. 但是亚马逊考试的问题和答案尚未更新。因此，根据AWS考试，选项C是正确答案。在文档中提出了在s3中请求率较高的情况下提高性能的建议。正确的答案是：在每个对象名称的前面加上十六进制哈希键以及当前数据。

Images will be retrieved infrequently, but must be available for retrieval immediately. Which is the MOST cost-efficient storage option that meets these requirements?
    1. Amazon Glacier with expedited retrievals
    2. Amazon S3 Standard-Infrequent Access          \(Correct\)
    3. Amazon EFs
    4. Amazon S3 Standard
18. Amazon S3 Infrequent Access is perfect if you want to store data that need not be frequently accessed. It is must more cost effective than Amazon S3 Standard \(Option D\). And if you choose Amazon Glacier with expedited retrievals, then you defeat the whole purpose of the requirement, because you would have an increased cost with this option. For more information on AWS Storage classes, please visit the following URL:
19. [https://aws.amazon.com/s3/storage-classes](https://aws.amazon.com/s3/storage-classes)

22. An application allows manufacturing sties to upload files. Each 3GB file is then processed to extract metadata, with the processing taking a few seconds for each file. The frequency updates is unpredictable - there may be no updates for hours, then several files uploaded concurrently. What architecture will address this workload the most cost efficiently?
    1. Use a Kinesis data delivery stream to store the file, and use Lambda for processing.
    2. Use an SQS queue to store the file, which is then accessed by a fleet of EC2 instances.          \(Wrong selected\)
    3. Store the file in an EBS volume, which can be accessed by another EC2 instance for processing.
    4. Store the file in an S3 bucket, and use Amazon S3 event notification to invoke a Lambda function to process the file.                  \(Correct\)
23. You can first create a Lambda function with the code to process the file. You can then use an Event Notification from the S3 bucket to invoke the Lambda function whenever a file is uploaded. For more information on Amazon S3 event notification, please visit the following URL: 
24. [https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonS3/latest/dev/NotificationHowTo.html](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonS3/latest/dev/NotificationHowTo.html)
25. 26. Option A is incorrect. Kinesis is used to collect, process and analyze real time data. 
27. The frequency of updates are quite unpredictable. By default SQS uses short polling. In this case, it will lead to the cost factor going up since we are getting messages in an unpredictable manner and many a times it will be returning empty responses. Hence option B is not a solution.
